column10: It's got issues, but for a F2P EA title it's not bad. Expect fortnite, but with... a specific goal?

The game is fun and unique. Just needs more players because the ques take about 5 mins and there is a gap of new players and players that are really good and they all get put in same matches so new players get stomped. But if you are naturally good at games and can grind through the pain of learning the game while professional gamers farm you then you will enjoy the game.
Some interesting ideas trying to mix BR game play with puzzles. But very rough around the edges.
